oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: May Day parade at Western State Hospital
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of a car decorated for the May Day parade at Western State Hospital. There are two unidentified women and one boy in the car, dressed in themed attire. The car is completely covered in flowers, ribbon and fabric.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Mental institutions; Automobiles; Children; Women; Parades & processions
